reviewText: Terrific cast, fine 1940s Monogram Pictures release produced by the star Kay Francis. The plot develops some good complexities in the last half, and has constant threatening menace throughout.
Kay Francis is always a pleasure to watch.  These movies are interesting to watch too because of the way society thought about life then.
Interesting fast-moving and super low-budget treatment of a scam story. Kay Francis, in her last film, is quite good - and also co-produced.
